      • getParallelBlockToExecute

        default BlockState getParallelBlockToExecute()

        Obtains the parallel BlockState to execute.

        This will not include the sequential BlockState instances. Therefore, this provides ability to check if a BlockState should be executed before this BlockState.

        Returns:
        Parallel BlockState to execute. May be null if no parallel BlockState to execute.

      • getNextBlockToExecute

        default BlockState getNextBlockToExecute()
        Obtains the next FunctionState to execute.
        Returns:
        Next FunctionState to execute. May be null if no further BlockState instances to execute.
